WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.900 --> 00:00:03.690
- Imagine you're stuck in a long meeting,

2
00:00:03.690 --> 00:00:06.660
and your coworker is taking
everyone's lunch order.

3
00:00:06.660 --> 00:00:08.400
You say you'd like a sandwich,

4
00:00:08.400 --> 00:00:11.790
and they end up ordering
you a tuna fish sandwich,

5
00:00:11.790 --> 00:00:14.130
which is not your thing.

6
00:00:14.130 --> 00:00:15.750
Since you didn't clearly communicate

7
00:00:15.750 --> 00:00:19.020
exactly what you wanted, you
didn't get a great outcome

8
00:00:19.020 --> 00:00:21.220
despite your coworker's
willingness to help.

9
00:00:22.320 --> 00:00:24.390
AI works similarly.

10
00:00:24.390 --> 00:00:27.870
It's best when you communicate
clearly to get what you want.

11
00:00:27.870 --> 00:00:30.360
You need to make sure you're
giving it detailed instructions

12
00:00:30.360 --> 00:00:32.100
and asking good questions.

13
00:00:32.100 --> 00:00:34.380
This is called prompting.

14
00:00:34.380 --> 00:00:37.350
When you prompt AI, there
are many ways to go about it,

15
00:00:37.350 --> 00:00:39.990
but the key principles are being clear

16
00:00:39.990 --> 00:00:42.240
and providing context.

17
00:00:42.240 --> 00:00:43.860
We'll start with a framework you can use

18
00:00:43.860 --> 00:00:45.840
to make sure your prompts
have clear directions

19
00:00:45.840 --> 00:00:47.670
and relevant information.

20
00:00:47.670 --> 00:00:49.260
This gives you a solid structure

21
00:00:49.260 --> 00:00:53.040
and guidelines for what to say
to AI so you aren't guessing.

22
00:00:53.040 --> 00:00:55.140
I'll show you how this works in Gemini.

23
00:00:55.140 --> 00:00:56.850
Consider this scenario.

24
00:00:56.850 --> 00:00:58.020
You're looking for advice

25
00:00:58.020 --> 00:01:00.990
on how to make a meeting more effective.

26
00:01:00.990 --> 00:01:08.520
We'll start by going to gemini.google.com.

27
00:01:08.520 --> 00:01:11.760
First, describe the persona
that you want Gemini to take on.

28
00:01:11.760 --> 00:01:13.920
That means decide what
expertise or knowledge

29
00:01:13.920 --> 00:01:15.360
you want Gemini to draw from

30
00:01:15.360 --> 00:01:17.730
before explaining what you want.

31
00:01:17.730 --> 00:01:19.590
In this example, you could tell Gemini

32
00:01:19.590 --> 00:01:22.890
to take on the persona of
someone who's highly experienced

33
00:01:22.890 --> 00:01:27.427
with large projects, which tend
to require lots of meetings.

34
00:01:27.427 --> 00:01:29.040
"You are a seasoned team leader

35
00:01:29.040 --> 00:01:32.880
with a proven track record
of managing large projects."

36
00:01:32.880 --> 00:01:36.907
Then describe a task you
want AI to help you with.

37
00:01:36.907 --> 00:01:39.990
"Give me some tips for running
more effective meetings."

38
00:01:39.990 --> 00:01:41.340
Next, specify the format

39
00:01:41.340 --> 00:01:43.500
by telling Gemini what the
output should look like.

40
00:01:43.500 --> 00:01:45.600
It could be a list of pros
and cons, bullet points,

41
00:01:45.600 --> 00:01:47.640
or a specific length or tone.

42
00:01:47.640 --> 00:01:51.357
Let's add, "Format your
response as a bullet list."

43
00:01:52.260 --> 00:01:53.670
Now you need to set the context.

44
00:01:53.670 --> 00:01:55.920
Ask yourself, what does AI need to know

45
00:01:55.920 --> 00:01:57.630
in order to get this right?

46
00:01:57.630 --> 00:02:00.840
For starters, AI doesn't know
how large your company is

47
00:02:00.840 --> 00:02:02.670
or how teams work together.

48
00:02:02.670 --> 00:02:04.650
It also doesn't know
your unique challenge,

49
00:02:04.650 --> 00:02:07.770
which is making clear decisions
during status meetings.

50
00:02:07.770 --> 00:02:12.570
We'll add, "Our teams often
work cross-functionally,

51
00:02:12.570 --> 00:02:14.550
and we're struggling
to make clear decisions

52
00:02:14.550 --> 00:02:18.267
on some aspects of the project
during our status meetings."

53
00:02:19.560 --> 00:02:21.000
One more note on the framework.

54
00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:24.270
There are plenty of ways to
construct an effective prompt.

55
00:02:24.270 --> 00:02:27.090
The order in which you construct
a prompt is less important

56
00:02:27.090 --> 00:02:29.370
than the substance of the prompt itself.

57
00:02:29.370 --> 00:02:31.743
Now let's run our prompt
and see what we get.

58
00:02:33.450 --> 00:02:34.283
Hmm.

59
00:02:35.520 --> 00:02:38.190
Okay, the idea of assigning
a dedicated decision maker

60
00:02:38.190 --> 00:02:40.440
and a note taker is interesting.

61
00:02:40.440 --> 00:02:42.690
It does help to know who has which role

62
00:02:42.690 --> 00:02:44.580
before the meeting starts.

63
00:02:44.580 --> 00:02:46.380
Make sure to check the output AI gives you

64
00:02:46.380 --> 00:02:47.640
before you use it.

65
00:02:47.640 --> 00:02:49.590
This is a crucial step.

66
00:02:49.590 --> 00:02:51.720
In some cases, the first
response you receive

67
00:02:51.720 --> 00:02:53.580
may have room for improvement.

68
00:02:53.580 --> 00:02:55.050
Maybe the different folks on my team

69
00:02:55.050 --> 00:02:56.160
work in different time zones,

70
00:02:56.160 --> 00:02:58.170
and it's hard to get the
dedicated decision maker

71
00:02:58.170 --> 00:03:01.230
in the meeting because it's
outside of their working hours.

72
00:03:01.230 --> 00:03:03.750
You can add this context
right into the same chat

73
00:03:03.750 --> 00:03:05.160
and ask it to update its advice

74
00:03:05.160 --> 00:03:07.170
based on the additional information.

75
00:03:07.170 --> 00:03:08.610
Prompting is a foundational skill

76
00:03:08.610 --> 00:03:11.010
for getting great results with AI.

77
00:03:11.010 --> 00:03:14.160
Here are a few more tips that
can help elevate your prompts.

78
00:03:14.160 --> 00:03:16.350
Provide an example or a reference.

79
00:03:16.350 --> 00:03:19.020
Just like seeing an example
helps you understand a task,

80
00:03:19.020 --> 00:03:21.813
giving one to AI helps
it understand your needs.

81
00:03:22.650 --> 00:03:24.510
If you're looking for
advice on running a meeting,

82
00:03:24.510 --> 00:03:27.390
attach a past agenda as a reference.

83
00:03:27.390 --> 00:03:28.680
It's also helpful to enlist

84
00:03:28.680 --> 00:03:31.140
Gemini's multimodal
capabilities when prompting

85
00:03:31.140 --> 00:03:33.990
to help it better understand
what you're looking for.

86
00:03:33.990 --> 00:03:35.820
This means including
different types of media

87
00:03:35.820 --> 00:03:38.763
in your prompt, like
documents, images, or websites.

88
00:03:39.720 --> 00:03:42.210
Think about how you would
communicate with a hairdresser.

89
00:03:42.210 --> 00:03:44.850
You might describe what
haircut you want using words,

90
00:03:44.850 --> 00:03:47.700
but sometimes showing a
picture can be more helpful.

91
00:03:47.700 --> 00:03:49.530
You can do the same with Gemini.

92
00:03:49.530 --> 00:03:51.060
You may need to use several prompts

93
00:03:51.060 --> 00:03:53.070
to keep on improving your output.

94
00:03:53.070 --> 00:03:55.650
This process is called iteration,

95
00:03:55.650 --> 00:03:57.570
and there's a few ways to do it.

96
00:03:57.570 --> 00:04:00.150
First, you can edit your initial prompt.

97
00:04:00.150 --> 00:04:02.400
For example, you can add more details

98
00:04:02.400 --> 00:04:05.520
to the persona, task, format, or context,

99
00:04:05.520 --> 00:04:08.040
or you can try writing a similar prompt

100
00:04:08.040 --> 00:04:09.870
with different phrasing.

101
00:04:09.870 --> 00:04:12.330
Another option, you can
break up your prompt

102
00:04:12.330 --> 00:04:13.860
into smaller parts.

103
00:04:13.860 --> 00:04:17.130
Instead of asking for a
full solution all in one go,

104
00:04:17.130 --> 00:04:18.870
you could first ask for principles

105
00:04:18.870 --> 00:04:21.000
of effective decision making.

106
00:04:21.000 --> 00:04:22.560
Then you could follow up

107
00:04:22.560 --> 00:04:24.330
and ask how you could
apply those principles

108
00:04:24.330 --> 00:04:25.650
in your meetings.

109
00:04:25.650 --> 00:04:28.320
Finally, you could ask
for a meeting agenda

110
00:04:28.320 --> 00:04:31.260
that will better enable decision making.

111
00:04:31.260 --> 00:04:32.820
This process helps AI

112
00:04:32.820 --> 00:04:36.150
to reason through each part
of the request at a time.

113
00:04:36.150 --> 00:04:37.770
You're focusing it on a smaller task

114
00:04:37.770 --> 00:04:39.630
and checking in along the way.

115
00:04:39.630 --> 00:04:43.230
Finally, you can add
constraints into your prompt.

116
00:04:43.230 --> 00:04:45.930
Constraints are requirements
that the AI should meet.

117
00:04:45.930 --> 00:04:48.570
For example, "Provide solutions

118
00:04:48.570 --> 00:04:50.100
that can be implemented within a week,"

119
00:04:50.100 --> 00:04:53.400
or, "Don't suggest
lengthening the meeting."

120
00:04:53.400 --> 00:04:54.810
Okay, one last tip.

121
00:04:54.810 --> 00:04:57.240
Remember to use one chat per topic.

122
00:04:57.240 --> 00:04:59.760
That's because everything
you enter into a single chat

123
00:04:59.760 --> 00:05:01.920
becomes context for AI.

124
00:05:01.920 --> 00:05:04.530
This is possible because
of long context windows,

125
00:05:04.530 --> 00:05:06.750
meaning you can keep the chat going

126
00:05:06.750 --> 00:05:09.300
and even return to it days or weeks later

127
00:05:09.300 --> 00:05:11.940
and pick up right where you left off.

128
00:05:11.940 --> 00:05:14.460
But if you switch to a new
topic in that same chat,

129
00:05:14.460 --> 00:05:16.710
things might get confused,

130
00:05:16.710 --> 00:05:20.070
so when changing topics,
always start a new chat.

131
00:05:20.070 --> 00:05:22.140
Putting this framework
and tips into practice

132
00:05:22.140 --> 00:05:24.630
is the key to effective prompting.

133
00:05:24.630 --> 00:05:26.460
This approach will help
you better guide AI

134
00:05:26.460 --> 00:05:28.890
towards the results
that you're looking for.

135
00:05:28.890 --> 00:05:30.900
And the more you practice, experiment,

136
00:05:30.900 --> 00:05:32.220
and get more comfortable,

137
00:05:32.220 --> 00:05:34.380
the better your results will become.

138
00:05:34.380 --> 00:05:36.630
Most importantly, as you
continue writing prompts

139
00:05:36.630 --> 00:05:38.340
for different types of tasks,

140
00:05:38.340 --> 00:05:40.290
the way you use AI will evolve

141
00:05:40.290 --> 00:05:42.090
from just giving it simple commands

142
00:05:42.090 --> 00:05:44.970
to having ongoing
collaborative conversations

143
00:05:44.970 --> 00:05:46.950
that add more value to your work.

144
00:05:46.950 --> 00:05:49.290
For example, once I planned a trip,

145
00:05:49.290 --> 00:05:50.790
and I found that it was really useful

146
00:05:50.790 --> 00:05:53.190
to add the ages of the
people who were traveling

147
00:05:53.190 --> 00:05:54.630
and then to return in the future

148
00:05:54.630 --> 00:05:56.580
when the dates changed to find out,

149
00:05:56.580 --> 00:05:58.530
did the itinerary that I had before work,

150
00:05:58.530 --> 00:06:00.240
or did it need to be updated?

151
00:06:00.240 --> 00:06:02.913
Ready to keep building
from here? Let's go.